name: Patrick Mahomes
summary: Patrick Mahomes, quarterback for the Kansas City Chiefs, has expressed discomfort with the tight schedule of playing three games within 11 days. He faces additional pressure with Myles Garrett pursuing him as his opponent. Despite his concerns about the impact on his body, Mahomes has dismissed his "biggest problem" as the Chiefs secure victories. However, recent reports indicate that Mahomes has sustained an ankle injury, rendering him week-to-week. In a game against the Browns, he was replaced by Carson Wentz after the injury. While the severity of the injury is not yet known, Chiefs HC has confirmed it is not broken. Mahomes remains day-to-day, but his status for upcoming games is uncertain.

name: Ashton Jeanty
summary: Boise State running back Ashton Jeanty recently made headlines after expressing his belief that he "should've walked away" with the Heisman Trophy. Jeanty was a finalist for the award but ultimately lost out to Travis Hunter. Despite this setback, Jeanty has been recognized for his stellar performance with two prestigious awards and has been praised for his impressive statistics, including outrushing 115 FBS teams. Some experts believe Jeanty may have had a stronger claim to the Heisman, while others support the decision to award it to Hunter. The debate surrounding Jeanty's Heisman candidacy has sparked discussions about his potential and the criteria for determining the winner of this prestigious award.
